<TITLE> PM leaves for Saudi Arabia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 20 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina left for Saudi Arabia just after midnight Monday on a five-day official visit. Her Bangladesh Biman flight took off for Riyadh at 12.05pm on and was expected to reach the Saudi capital around five hours later. Hasina met with president Md Zillur Rahman at Bangabhaban earlier in the day, to discuss the Saudi trip, in her first visit with the head of state since he returned from Singapore after treatment on Apr 15, an aide said. She was seen off at the airport by cabinet members Sahara Kahtun, AMA Muhith, Motia Chowdhury, Abdul Latif Biswas and the three chiefs of staff among others. Foreign minister Dipu Moni and her state minister Hasan Mahmud, expatriates welfare minister Khandker Musharraf Hossain and state minister Monnuzan Sufian are flying with Sheikh Hasina. Her sister Sheikh Rehana and son Sajib Wazed Joy are also accompanying the prime minister on the tripher first official overseas visit since taking office as prime minister on Jan 6. The prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad and a member of the entourage told bdnews24.com that the delegation comprises some 34 members. In addition to meeting Saudi King, the prime minister will perform Umrah, according to foreign ministry officials. Hasina is scheduled to meet King Abdullah bin Abdullah Aziz Al Saud in Riyadh on Tuesday morning, Hasan Mahmud told bdnews24.com. "We will perform Umrah next day in Mecca." "We will also meet the Saudi labour minister, but the time and venue will be fixed after reaching Saudi Arabia," he said. Saudi home to 2m Bangladeshis Bangladesh is highly dependent on foreign remittances from around 20 lakh (2 million) Bangladeshis living and working in Saudi Arabia. Bangladeshis are the largest group of foreign nationals in the kingdom. In 2007, around 30 percent of Bangladesh's total $6.56 billion in remittance came from the country. In 2008, a similar percentage of the total of $ 9 billion came from the kingdom. Riyadh last year banned unskilled Bangladeshi manpower in some sectors. Foreign ministry officials have told bdnews24.com that Sheikh Hasina will go to Madina on the third day of her visit to offer Fatiha at the tomb of the Prophet Mohammad (SM). She will return to Mecca and then visit Jeddah. The prime minister is scheduled to leave Jeddah for Dhaka on April 25 morning and land in Dhaka at 2.00pm. bdn
